bug.short_desc: [abrt] gnome-software: magazine_chain_pop_head(): gnome-software killed by SIGSEGV

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Install F24 Alpha candidate 7 (Alpha-1.7) Workstation x86_64 live to a KVM, boot installed system, create user in g-i-s, leave system sitting at desktop for a bit (I'd guess it's crashing during check for available updates, I don't see an update notification and I should).
Version-Release number of selected component: gnome-software-3.19.91-2.fc24
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.6.4 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/bin/gnome-software --gapplication-service crash_function: magazine_chain_pop_head executable: /usr/bin/gnome-software global_pid: 2193 kernel: 4.5.0-0.rc7.git0.2.fc24.x86_64 runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 magazine_chain_pop_head at gslice.c:539 #1 magazine_cache_trim at gslice.c:678 #2 magazine_cache_push_magazine at gslice.c:710 #3 thread_memory_magazine2_unload at gslice.c:809 #4 g_slice_free1 at gslice.c:1118 #5 g_list_free_1 at glist.c:203 #6 g_queue_pop_head at gqueue.c:521 #7 continue_writing at gdbusprivate.c:1424 #8 continue_writing_in_idle_cb at gdbusprivate.c:1516 #13 gdbus_shared_thread_func at gdbusprivate.c:246
Potential duplicate: bug 1044730

As this appears to prevent 'updates available' notifications (at least at first glance), proposing as a Final blocker: "Release-blocking desktops must notify the user of available updates, but must not do so when running as a live image."

Discussed at today's blocker review meeting [1]. Voted as AcceptedBlocker (Final) - this appears to violate "Release-blocking desktops must notify the user of available updates, but must not do so when running as a live image."
[1] https://meetbot-raw.fedoraproject.org/fedora-blocker-review/2016-03-29
I tested this today, no crash, software updates popup appeared. I assume it's probably fixed now. There are no more crashes shown in FAF either. Please reopen if you can reproduce.
